"called categories. You can create your own categories, called User "
"Categories, which are useful for organizing items. For example, you can use "
"the User Categories Editor (click the Manage User Categories button) to "
"create a user category called Favorite Authors, then put the items for your "
"favorites into the category. User categories can have sub-categories. For "
"example, the user category Favorites.Authors is a sub-category of Favorites."
" You might also have Favorites.Series, in which case there will be two sub-"
"categories under Favorites. Sub-categories can be created by right-clicking "
"on a user category, choosing \"Add sub-category to ...\", and entering the "
"sub-category name; or by using the User Categories Editor by entering names "
"like the Favorites example above."
